---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About · __SITE_NAME__" description="About this Astro template.">
  <header style="text-align: center;">
    <h1 style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 5vw, 2.5rem); margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">About</h1>
  </header>
  <div style="max-width: 60ch; margin: 0 auto; color: var(--fg);">
    <p>
      This page proves base-aware routing works. The nav links are built from
      <code>import.meta.env.BASE_URL</code>, so they point at
      <code>/REPO/about/</code> on a project site and <code>/about/</code> on a
      user site — without you changing anything.
    </p>
    <p>
      Edit <code>src/pages/</code> to add pages, <code>src/components/</code> for
      reusable UI, and <code>src/layouts/Layout.astro</code> for the shell.
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
